<article id="node-16912">
<h1 >3.5.1.130 Supplementary benefits &amp; employment assistance for PP recipients</h1>
<h2>Other benefits - <a href="../../../acronyms#pps" title="Parenting payment (single)">PPS</a> recipients</h2>
<p>A PPS recipient MAY also qualify for other assistance, if they meet the relevant qualification criteria. The benefits that may be applicable are:</p>
<ul><li>rent assistance (<a href="../../../1/2/7/10">1.2.7.10</a>)</li>
<li>pharmaceutical allowance (<a href="../../../1/2/7/20">1.2.7.20</a>)</li>
<li>telephone allowance (<a href="../../../1/2/7/70">1.2.7.70</a>)</li>
<li>crisis payment (<a href="../../../1/2/6/30">1.2.6.30</a>)</li>
<li>energy supplement (<a href="../../../1/2/12/20">1.2.12.20</a>)</li>
<li>remote area allowance (<a href="../../../1/2/7/80">1.2.7.80</a>)</li>
<li>bereavement payment (<a href="../../1/5.1">3.1.5</a>)</li>
<li>pensioner concession card (<a href="../../../1/2/8/20">1.2.8.20</a>)
<ul><li>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example:</strong> During an employment income nil rate period a recipient can keep their <a href="../../../acronyms#pcc" title="Pensioner concession card">PCC</a>.</p>
</div>
</li>
</ul></li>
<li>in some cases, a <a href="../../../acronyms#hcc" title="Health care card">HCC</a> (<a href="../../../1/2/8/10">1.2.8.10</a>)
<ul><li>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example:</strong> A recipient who has been receiving an income support payment continuously for a period of at least 12 months then ceases to qualify for PPS because of income from employment. The recipient is entitled to a HCC for 6 months from the date of cancellation of payment (however if they have kept their PCC for the employment income nil rate period, they are entitled to a HCC for the balance of the 6 months).</p>
</div>
</li>
</ul></li>
<li>pension supplement if over age pension age (<a href="../../../1/2/10/10">1.2.10.10</a>)</li>
<li>pension supplement basic amount if under age pension age</li>
<li>education entry payment (<a href="../../../1/2/7/60">1.2.7.60</a>)</li>
<li><a href="../../../acronyms#apws" title="Approved program of work supplement">APWS</a> for recipients participating in the following activities; <a href="../../../acronyms#wfd" title="Work for the Dole">WFD</a>, <a href="../../../acronyms#nwep" title="National Work Experience Programme">NWEP</a> or <a href="../../../acronyms#cdp" title="Community Development Program">CDP</a> structured activities</li>
<li>language, literacy and numeracy training and supplement (<a href="../../../1/2/7/110">1.2.7.110</a>)</li>
<li>pensioner education supplement (<a href="../../../1/2/7/30">1.2.7.30</a>)</li>
<li><a href="../../../acronyms#ftb" title="Family tax benefit">FTB</a> Part A (FA Guide <a href="../../../../family-assistance-guide/1/2/1">1.2.1</a>)</li>
<li>FTB Part B (FA Guide <a href="../../../../family-assistance-guide/1/2/1">1.2.1</a>)</li>
<li>child care subsidy (FA Guide <a href="../../../../family-assistance-guide/1/2/6">1.2.6</a>)</li>
<li>additional child care subsidy (FA Guide <a href="../../../../family-assistance-guide/1/2/7">1.2.7</a>)</li>
<li>stillborn baby payment (FA Guide <a href="../../../../family-assistance-guide/1/2/19">1.2.19</a>).</li>
</ul><div class="reference">
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> SS Guide <a href="../../9/1/10">3.9.1.10</a> Qualification for HCC - automatic issue, <a href="../../15/2.1">3.15.2</a> ES - qualification &amp; payability</p>
</div>
<h2>Other benefits - <a href="../../../acronyms#ppp" title="Parenting payment (partnered)">PPP</a> recipients</h2>
<p>A PPP recipient MAY also qualify for other benefits, if they meet the relevant qualification criteria. The benefits that may be applicable are:</p>
<ul><li>rent assistance (<a href="../../../1/2/7/10">1.2.7.10</a>)</li>
<li><a href="../../../acronyms#pha" title="Pharmaceutical allowance">PhA</a> in some cases (<a href="../../../1/2/7/20">1.2.7.20</a>)
<ul><li>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example:</strong> A recipient aged over 60 but under age pension age who has been receiving an income support payment for a continuous period of at least 9 months.</p>
</div>
</li>
</ul></li>
<li><a href="../../../acronyms#tal" title="Telephone allowance">TAL</a> in some cases (<a href="../../../1/2/7/70">1.2.7.70</a>)</li>
<li>crisis payment (<a href="../../../1/2/6/30">1.2.6.30</a>)</li>
<li>energy supplement (<a href="../../../1/2/12/20">1.2.12.20</a>)</li>
<li>bereavement payment (<a href="../../1/5.1">3.1.5</a>)</li>
<li>remote area allowance (<a href="../../../1/2/7/80">1.2.7.80</a>)</li>
<li>health care card (<a href="../../../1/2/8/10">1.2.8.10</a>)
<ul><li>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example:</strong> During an employment income nil rate period a recipient can retain their HCC.</p>
</div>
</li>
</ul></li>
<li>in some cases, a PCC (<a href="../../../1/2/8/20">1.2.8.20</a>)
<ul><li>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example:</strong> A recipient aged over 60 years who has received an income support payment continuously for a period of at least 9 months. If such a recipient is holding a PCC and their payment is cancelled due to the employment of themselves or their partner, the person can retain the PCC for 6 months from the date of cancellation.</p>
</div>
</li>
</ul></li>
<li>pension supplement if over age pension age (<a href="../../../1/2/10/10">1.2.10.10</a>)</li>
<li>education entry payment (<a href="../../../1/2/7/60">1.2.7.60</a>)</li>
<li>APWS for recipients participating in the following activities; WFD, NWEP or CDP structured activities</li>
<li>language, literacy and numeracy training and supplement (<a href="../../../1/2/7/110">1.2.7.110</a>)</li>
<li><a href="../../../acronyms#pes" title="Pensioner education supplement">PES</a> (<a href="../../../1/2/7/30">1.2.7.30</a>) (in certain circumstances)</li>
<li>FTB Part A (FA Guide <a href="../../../../family-assistance-guide/1/2/1">1.2.1</a>)</li>
<li>FTB Part B (FA Guide <a href="../../../../family-assistance-guide/1/2/1">1.2.1</a>)</li>
<li>child care subsidy (FA Guide <a href="../../../../family-assistance-guide/1/2/6">1.2.6</a>)</li>
<li>additional child care subsidy (FA Guide <a href="../../../../family-assistance-guide/1/2/7">1.2.7</a>)</li>
<li>stillborn baby payment (FA Guide <a href="../../../../family-assistance-guide/1/2/19">1.2.19</a>).</li>
</ul><div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A04121" title="Social Security Act 1991">SSAct</a> section 1068B-E1 Qualification for PhA - benefit PP (partnered), section 1068A-C1 Qualification for PhA - pension PP (single), section 1068A-F1 RAA - pension PP (single), section 1068B-G1 RAA - benefit PP (partnered), section 1061Q(1) Qualification for TAL, section 1061Q(3) Qualification for TAL, section 665A Payment to recipient of pension PP (single) - EdEP, section 665ZU Payment to recipient of PP (partnered) - EdEP, section 1061PJ(2) Payments attracting PES, section 1061ZK Qualification: general rules (HCC), section 1061ZMA Further extended qualification rule: loss of payment because of employment income, section 1061ZA General qualification rules (PCC), section 1061ZEA Further extended qualification rule: loss of payment because of employment income, section 1070A Effect of this Part (RA)</p>
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> SS Guide <a href="../../11/2">3.11.2</a> Job Plans, <a href="../../8/2.1">3.8.2</a> PhA - qualification &amp; payability, <a href="../../8/1.1">3.8.1</a> RA - qualification &amp; payability, <a href="../../8/8.1">3.8.8</a> RAA - qualification &amp; payability, <a href="../../8/7.1">3.8.7</a> TAL - qualification &amp; payability, <a href="../../12/1">3.12.1</a> Pension supplement - qualification &amp; payability, <a href="../../8/6.1">3.8.6</a> EdEP - Qualification &amp; Payability, <a href="../../8/3.1">3.8.3</a> PES - Qualification &amp; Payability, <a href="../../9/1.1">3.9.1</a> HCC - Qualification Provisions, <a href="../../9/2.1">3.9.2</a> PCC - Qualification Provisions, <a href="../../7/4.1">3.7.4</a> CrP - qualification &amp; payability, <a href="../../15/1">3.15.1</a> CEA - qualification &amp; payability, <a href="../../15/2.1">3.15.2</a> ES - qualification &amp; payability</p>
</div>
<h2>Employment incentives</h2>
<p><a href="../../../acronyms#pp" title="Parenting payment">PP</a> recipients may receive the following incentives to take up a job:</p>
<ul><li>access to working credits</li>
<li>payment of certain supplementary benefits during the employment income nil rate period</li>
<li>continued use of their HCC or PCC for a certain period, and</li>
<li>able to have their payment resumed during the employment income nil rate period if they report a fall in income sufficient for PP to be payable again.</li>
</ul><div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A04121" title="Social Security Act 1991">SSAct</a> section 23(4A) Despite subsection (4) …, section 23(4AA) For the purposes of subsection (4A) …, section 1061ZMA Further extended qualification rule: loss of payment because of employment income, section 1061ZEA Further extended qualification rule: loss of payment because of employment income, section 1061ZA General qualification rules (PCC), section 1061ZK Qualification: general rules (HCC)</p>
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> SS Guide <a href="../../1/11.1">3.1.11</a> Working credit, <a href="../../1/12">3.1.12</a> Employment income nil rate period, <a href="../../9/1/10">3.9.1.10</a> Qualification for HCC - automatic issue, <a href="../../9/2/30">3.9.2.30</a> PCC due to employment</p>
</div>
